  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. This package is a synthetic adversarial sample targeting W-AR-05: one validation result omits the comparedAgainst link; a second result references a cannulated-construct dataset whose test geometry differs from the declared non-cannulated COU, constituting an undercutting inference-method mismatch (D3).",
