      "rationale": "An independent FEA analyst at each of the three ensemble sites performed a blind review of boundary condition definitions, material card assignments, and contact pair formulations. Discrepancies identified during review (minor: rod pre-tension magnitude, friction coefficient assignment) were resolved prior to final simulation runs. No systematic use errors were identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The constitutive model must account for nonlinear (bilinear isotropic hardening) titanium alloy behaviour. Geometric nonlinearity must be enabled for all load steps exceeding 5 mm displacement. Contact formulation must be augmented Lagrangian or penalty with documented coefficient selection.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material response modelled with bilinear isotropic hardening (E = 113.8 GPa, sigma_y = 880 MPa, E_t = 1.1 GPa) consistent with published coupon data. NLGEOM enabled throughout. Augmented Lagrangian contact with normal stiffness factor 1.0 and friction coefficient 0.2 (PEEK-Ti interface) applied at screw-head and rod-saddle interfaces. Model form uncertainty contribution estimated at 3.1% of stiffness QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material property distributions must be derived from lot-specific coupon testing or peer-reviewed published distributions. Geometric dimensions must be measured from the actual test specimens using CMM or equivalent, with tolerances propagated through the model.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and yield strength distributions derived from N=6 tensile coupons machined from the same Ti-6Al-4V bar stock as the test constructs. CMM measurements of screw shank diameter, rod diameter, and inter-screw span recorded for each of the N=11 specimens; mean and standard deviation propagated as input uncertainty. UHMWPE block material properties taken from published compressive modulus data (Kurtz 2009)."
    },
    {
