      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production lots were tested: N=6 at Laboratory 1 (FDA CDRH biomechanics lab) and N=5 at Laboratory 2 (DePuy Synthes test facility). Manufacturing lot certificates of conformance and dimensional inspection reports retained. Inter-laboratory variability in stiffness was 2.3% (CV), consistent with normal production scatter."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate all ASTM F1717 required parameters (loading rate, fixture geometry, environmental conditioning) and must span at least two rod diameters or two inter-screw spans to confirm model generalisability across the COU parameter space.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 protocol followed at both laboratories (loading rate 25 mm/min, standard UHMWPE blocks, ambient temperature). However, all N=11 constructs used a single inter-screw span of 44 mm and a single rod diameter of 5.5 mm. The COU encompasses the broader pedicle screw construct design space; testing at a single geometric configuration limits confidence that the model generalises across span and rod diameter variations. This factor is assessed below required level and is noted as a limitation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions, loading) must be demonstrably matched to the experimental test configuration. Any deviations must be documented and their effect on QoI estimated.",
      "rationale": "Specimen-specific CMM dimensions were used to parameterise each of the N=11 simulation instances. Material properties matched to lot-specific coupon data. Boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture constraints (fixed inferior block, axial-angular load applied to superior block at 5-degree offset). One deviation noted: simulated loading head geometry is idealised as rigid flat surface; actual fixture has a 12 mm radius spherical seat. Sensitivity analysis showed < 0.5% effect on stiffness QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric must account for both model prediction uncertainty and experimental measurement uncertainty. Acceptance criterion E/uval < 1.96 must be applied to all primary QoIs.",
      "rationale": "E/uval metric applied per ASME V&V 40 Section 5. Experimental uncertainty uexp estimated from inter-specimen variability (N=11) and inter-laboratory variability. Model prediction uncertainty unum estimated from mesh convergence, input parameter propagation, and inter-solver ensemble spread. Combined uval = sqrt(uexp^2 + unum^2). Results: stiffness E/uval = 1.31, yield force E/uval = 1.18, force at 40 mm E/uval = 1.44 (from cannulated comparator dataset — see validation result VR-002). All below 1.96 threshold."
    },
    {
