      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validated QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) must be directly traceable to the regulatory submission claims and to the failure modes identified in the device risk analysis.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are the primary performance endpoints in the 510(k) substantial equivalence argument. Force at 40 mm displacement is a secondary endpoint used to characterise post-yield energy absorption. All three QoIs are explicitly listed in the device design verification and validation plan and map to the fatigue and static strength failure modes in the device FMEA."
