      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation scenario (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending, non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw, N=11, two laboratories) must be judged as representative of the intended use scenario with respect to loading mode, construct geometry, and material system.",
      "rationale": "The validation scenario directly replicates the regulatory test standard (ASTM F1717) applied to the specific device geometry and material system under review. Loading mode (compression-bending), screw diameter (7.5 mm), and construct configuration are identical to the COU. The use of two independent laboratories mitigates laboratory-specific artefacts. The single inter-screw span and rod diameter (noted under Test conditions) represent a minor limitation but do not disqualify the validation activity from being considered representative of the COU at the Medium assurance level."
